# HR Analytics Dashboard using Power BI

## Objective
The objective of this project is to analyze employee attrition data and build an interactive HR Analytics Dashboard using Microsoft Power BI. The dashboard provides insights into employee attrition across different departments, job roles, gender, and age groups.

---

## Tools Used
- Microsoft Power BI Desktop
- Power Query
- DAX (Data Analysis Expressions)

---

## Dataset
IBM HR Analytics Employee Attrition Dataset

---

## Data Cleaning
The following preprocessing steps were performed:

- Imported HR employee dataset into Power BI.
- Checked data types for all columns.
- Removed duplicate records.
- Verified missing values.
- Created Age Group using DAX.
- Prepared dataset for visualization.

---

## DAX Formula Used

### Age Group

```DAX
Age Group =
SWITCH(
TRUE(),
'WA_Fn-UseC_-HR-Employee-Attrition'[Age] <=30,"18-30",
'WA_Fn-UseC_-HR-Employee-Attrition'[Age] <=40,"31-40",
'WA_Fn-UseC_-HR-Employee-Attrition'[Age] <=50,"41-50",
"51+"
)
```

---

## Dashboard KPIs

- Total Employees
- Average Age
- Average Monthly Income

---

## Visualizations

- Employee Attrition Overview
- Attrition by Department
- Attrition by Job Role


## Interactive Filters

- Department
- Gender
- Age Group

---

## Key Insights

- Research & Development department has the highest number of employees.
- Majority of employees have not left the organization.
- Some job roles experience significantly higher attrition.
- Most employees belong to the age group 31–40 years.
- Dashboard allows dynamic filtering using slicers.

